
  Performs Evaluations.
  Provides technical guidance and instruction to staff in relationship to Document Control Policies.
  Provide updates/reports on project status.
  Reviews projects document requirement list and do the submission.
  Submits required documents punctually and with quality.
  Ensures that all required documents are well checked and submitted on time.
  Distributes and monitors the documents submitted for revisions and approval, and preparing &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the final documentation for project.
  Organizes and manages hard and soft copies of project documents per order.
  Liaises to all the Department Manager’s or Supervisors for issues and concerns.
  Supervises the preparation of Testing Documents such as FAT Procedure and matrices for Technicians perusal.
  Supervises and ensures accuracy of all documentation.
  Attends project order meetings with customers.
